404→                           Erdős and Moser <a href="#cite-Er65-362" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er65','362'); return false;">[Er65]</a> proved the first bound with an additional factor of $(\log n)^{3/2}$. This was removed by Sárközy and Szemerédi <a href="#cite-SaSz65-362" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('SaSz65','362'); return false;">[SaSz65]</a>, thereby answering the first question in the affirmative. Stanley <a href="#cite-St80-362" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('St80','362'); return false;">[St80]</a> has shown that this quantity is maximised when $A=\{-\lfloor \frac{N-1}{2}\rfloor,\ldots,\lfloor\frac{N}{2}\rfloor\}$.<br><br>The second question was answered in the affirmative by Halász <a href="#cite-Ha77-362" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Ha77','362'); return false;">[Ha77]</a>, as a consequence of a more general multi-dimensional result.
